2) cost_of_the_order: Below are cost of the food order price: minimum - 4.47 average - 14.4 maximum - 35.7 most foods are sold between 12 rs to 17 rs.
3) delivery_time: Below are time taken to delivery the food: minimum - 15 minutes average - 25 minutes maximum - 33 minuetes, overall it is right skewed, means most of the foods are deliveries are fast and few take long.

4) rating: Below are the ratings given to each category of orders: Not given - 38.78% 5 - 30.98% 4 - 20.34% 3 - 9.91%

5) cuisine_type: As per count plot, Among the top cuisines, American has the highest number of orders, followed by Japanese, Italian, and Chinese. Other cuisine types have fewer orders in comparison to these top categories.

6)day_of_the_week: As per the count plot, the majority of orders occur during the weekends, indicating higher customer activity on weekends compared to weekdays.

7)restaurant_name: The restaurant_name column contains a large number of unique values, making it difficult to analyze all restaurants individually. To simplify the analysis, a pie chart was created using the top 5 restaurants based on the number of orders.Among them, Shake Shack received the highest number of orders, followed by The Meatball Shop, Blue Ribbon Sushi, and Parm. This indicates that these restaurants are the most preferred among customers in the dataset.

8) order_id : it is just an identifier, do not provider a meaningful insights out of it when we plot them individually.

9) customer_id: Large peak between 40,000 and 150,000 indicating a large group of earlier customers. and second smaller peak between 320,000 and 400,000 suggesting a newer wave of customers. in between these two groups (around 150,000 to 300,000), there's a significant dip in customer count, showing lower customer acquisition or engagement during that period.

Question 13: The company wants to provide a promotional offer in the advertisement of the restaurants. The condition to get the offer is that the restaurants must have a rating count of more than 50 and the average rating should be greater than 4. Find the restaurants fulfilling the criteria to get the promotional offer. [3 marks]¶

In [18]:
# Write the code here

rating_count = df.groupby('restaurant_name')['rating'].count()
rating_mean = df.groupby('restaurant_name')['rating'].mean()

rating_count_filter = rating_count>50
rating_mean_filter = rating_mean>4

final_filter = rating_count_filter & rating_mean_filter
final_filter
eligible_restaurants = rating_count.index[final_filter]
eligible_restaurants

Index(['Blue Ribbon Fried Chicken', 'Blue Ribbon Sushi', 'Shake Shack',

Question 14: The company charges the restaurant 25% on the orders having cost greater than 20 dollars and 15% on the orders having cost greater than 5 dollars. Find the net revenue generated by the company across all orders. [3 marks]¶

In [23]:
# Write the code here
conditions =[
    df['cost_of_the_order']>20,
    (df['cost_of_the_order']>5) & (df['cost_of_the_order']<=20)
]

choices = [
    df['cost_of_the_order']*0.25,
    df['cost_of_the_order']*0.15
]

df['revenue'] = np.select(conditions, choices, default=0)
net_revenue = df['revenue'].sum()
print(net_revenue)

6166.303

Observations:¶

the net revenue generated by the company across all orders is $6166.303

Conclusion and Recommendations¶

Question 17: What are your conclusions from the analysis? What recommendations would you like to share to help improve the business? (You can use cuisine type and feedback ratings to drive your business recommendations.) [6 marks]¶

### Conclusions:

  • The average delivery time is shorter on weekends (22 mins) compared to weekdays (28 mins). This is may be due to better staffing or lesser traffic.

  • Spanish, Thai, and Indian cuisines received the highest average ratings, suggesting these are the most well-liked by customers. On the other hand, Vietnamese and Korean cuisines have relatively lower average ratings, indicating slightly lower customer satisfaction compared to other cuisines.

  • The average delivery time decreases the customer rating tends to increases, . This means that faster delivery is associated with higher customer satisfaction.

  • Southern, French, and Spanish cuisines have the highest average order costs

  • Most people like to have American and Japanese cusinies more during weekends. compared to weekdays.

  • looks like the low rating restaurant ex: Hunan manor, wichcraft got good rating during weekday but not in the weekends.

  • The data reveals that the number of orders is noticeably higher on weekends compared to weekdays. This trend suggests that customers prefer to order food more frequently during weekends, likely due to leisure time, social gatherings, or a break from routine cooking.

  • It is evident that cuisines such as Spanish, French, Southern, and Thai receive significantly fewer orders compared to more popular cuisines like Japanese, American, and Italian. One notable factor contributing to this difference is pricing, the less popular cuisines tend to have higher average prices, which may be discourging the customers from ordering them frequently.

Recommendations:¶

  • In Delivery : Improve Weekday Delivery Times. -> Weekday deliveries take 5.87 minutes longer than weekends. To fix that, Shift more delivery staff to weekday peak rush hours.

  • Improve Low-Rated but High-Volume Cuisines -> Indian and Mexican cuisines generate high order volumes and revenue but have lower ratings.

  • Low-rated restaurants like Hunan Manor and Wichcraft perform better on weekdays than weekends, that signals an inconsistency in service or experience. Investigate differences in staffing, menu, or kitchen load on weekends.Ensure key weekday staff or chefs are also involved in weekend shifts

  • the weekday sales is less compared to weekend sales. need to improve on the weekday sales to do that. Increase advertising efforts specifically in business districts and office hubs. This includes promoting partner restaurants through banners, digital ads, and in-app promotions during office hours. Offer corporate meal plans or subscription-based weekday lunch deliveries at a discounted rate for employees working in offices, tech parks, or co-working spaces.

  • Observation shows that Spanish, French, Southern, and Thai cuisines have fewer orders compared to Japanese, American, and Italian, likely due to higher prices. To improve sales, FoodHub can offer discounts or combo deals on these cuisines and promote them through app highlights to attract more weekday customers.
